<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Los Angeles Trade and Technical College</h2>
<strong>Los Angeles, CA</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Credit granted for scores of 3 or better on a variety of Advanced Placement Exams. Students should file a General Petition in the Admissions and Records Office and have an official copy of test results sent to the college. To be eligible for AP credit a student must be enrolled at LATTC during the semester when credit is granted, have completed a minimum of 12 units of credit at LATTC and have a GPA of 2.0 or higher. The maximum number of units allowable toward the AA/AS Degree is 15. For Course units and equivalency, contact the Admissions Office.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.lattc.edu/lattc/catalog0304/catalog_academic_standards.htm" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

